<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 25 at 5:49AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Periods of snow and blowing snow through Friday morning...
Periods of light snow will continue on the Rocky Mountain Front
through tonight into Friday morning. It likely will not be a
persistent snowfall, but one to two inches of total snowfall are
expected on Marias Pass, while 2 to 5 inches of snow are likely
above mountain pass level. Westerly winds will also increase to
between 25 and 35 mph with gusts to 50 mph during the afternoon
and evening hours, causing reduced visibility in blowing snow.
Those traveling in this region should be alert for the potential
for rapidly reduced visibility and changing road conditions,
especially over Marias Pass.</description>
